quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  16,103,"We surely know that they say, “It is only a human being who teaches him.” But the language they refer to is foreign, whereas this is eloquent Arabic language."
  16,104,"Those who do not believe in the verses of Allah, Allah will not guide them, and for them there will be a painful punishment."
  16,105,"No one fabricates lies except those who do not believe in the verses of Allah; it is they who are the liars."
  16,106,"Whoever disbelieves in Allah after having believed – except one who is compelled while his heart is firm in faith – but those who embrace disbelief willingly, upon them will be the wrath of Allah, and for them there will be a great punishment."
  16,107,"That is because they prefer the life of this world to the Hereafter, and Allah does not guide the disbelieving people."
  16,108,"These are the ones whose hearts, hearing and sight are sealed up by Allah; it is they who are the heedless."
  16,109,"No doubt that it is they who will be the greatest losers in the Hereafter."
  16,110,"As for those who emigrated after being persecuted, then strove [for the cause of Allah], and were patient – indeed, your Lord is after that All-Forgiving, Most Merciful."